  "content": "**Here are six AI startups meeting the criteria (mega funding rounds over $1B or $10B+ valuations achieved via 2026 activity), based on reported events through mid-2026:**[[1]](https://techcrunch.com/2026/02/17/here-are-the-17-us-based-ai-companies-that-have-raised-100m-or-more-in-2026/)[[2]](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2026-05-27/ai-startup-cognition-raises-1b-at-26b-valuation-video)\n\n- **xAI**: Raised $20 billion (Series E, January 2026); Elon Musk’s AI lab developing advanced models toward AGI.[[1]](https://techcrunch.com/2026/02/17/here-are-the-17-us-based-ai-companies-that-have-raised-100m-or-more-in-2026/)\n- **Anthropic**: Raised $30 billion (Series G at ~$380 billion post-money valuation, February 2026); develops safety-focused frontier AI models like Claude.[[1]](https://techcrunch.com/2026/02/17/here-are-the-17-us-based-ai-companies-that-have-raised-100m-or-more-in-2026/)[[3]](https://www.crescendo.ai/news/latest-vc-investment-deals-in-ai-startups)\n- **OpenAI**: Raised $122 billion (record round at ~$852 billion post-money valuation, March 2026); builds leading generative AI models and products (e.g., GPT series).[[4]](https://intellizence.com/insights/startup-funding/top-startup-funding-deals-of-q1-2026-record-297-billion-raised-with-ai-dominating/)[[3]](https://www.crescendo.ai/news/latest-vc-investment-deals-in-ai-startups)\n- **Skild AI**: Raised $1.4 billion (Series C at $14 billion valuation, January 2026); develops AI models to power robotics and embodied AI.[[1]](https://techcrunch.com/2026/02/17/here-are-the-17-us-based-ai-companies-that-have-raised-100m-or-more-in-2026/)\n- **Cognition** (Devin AI coding agent): Raised over $1 billion (at $26 billion valuation, May 2026); creates AI agents for software development and coding.[[2]](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2026-05-27/ai-startup-cognition-raises-1b-at-26b-valuation-video)\n- **Nscale**: Raised $2 billion (Series C at $14.6 billion valuation, March 2026); builds AI-optimized data center and cloud infrastructure/hyperscale compute.[[5]](https://www.nscale.com/press-releases/nscale-series-c)[[6]](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/03/09/nscale-ai-data-center-nvidia-raise.html)\n\nThese primarily reflect Q1 2026 mega-rounds amid the AI boom, with additional examples like World Labs ($1 billion round in February 2026 for spatial/world models) also qualifying on funding size.[[7]](https://www.worldlabs.ai/blog/funding-2026)[[8]](https://www.reuters.com/business/ai-pioneer-fei-fei-lis-world-labs-raises-1-billion-funding-2026-02-18/) Valuations and raises can shift with new reports; figures are drawn from contemporaneous news.",
